quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  42,27,"Should God bestow abundance upon his servants, they might act wantonly on the earth: but He sendeth down what He will by measure; for he knoweth, beholdeth his servants"
  42,28,"He it is who after that men have despaired of it, sendeth down the rain, and spreadeth abroad his mercy: He is the Protector, the Praiseworthy"
  42,29,"Among his signs is the creation of the Heavens and of the Earth, and the creatures which he hath scattered over both: and, for their gathering together when he will, He is allpowerful"
  42,30,"Nor happeneth to you any mishap, but it is for your own handy-work: and yet he forgiveth many things"
  42,31,"Ye cannot weaken him on the earth: neither, beside God, patron or helper shall ye have"
  42,32,Among his signs also are the sea-traversing ships like mountains
  42,33,"if such be his will, He lulleth the wind, and they lie motionless on the back of the waves: - truly herein are signs to all the constant, the grateful"
  42,34,"Or if, for their ill deserts, He cause them to founder, still He forgiveth much"
  42,35,But they who gainsay our signs shall know that there will be no escape for them
  42,36,"All that you receive is but for enjoyment in this life present: but better and more enduring is a portion with God, for those who believe and put their trust in their Lord"
  42,37,"And who avoid the heinous things of crime, and filthiness, and when they are angered, forgive"
  42,38,"And who hearken to their Lord, and observe prayer, and whose affairs are guided by mutual COUNSEL, and who give alms of that with which we have enriched them"
  42,39,"And who, when a wrong is done them, redress themselves"
  42,40,"Yet let the recompense of evil be only a like evil but he who forgiveth and is reconciled, shall be rewarded by God himself; for He loveth not those who act unjustly"
  42,41,"And there shall be no way open against those who, after being wronged, avenge themselves"
  42,42,"But there shall be a way open against those who unjustly wrong others, and act insolently on the earth in disregard of justice. These! a grievous punishment doth await them"
  42,43,And whoso beareth wrongs with patience and forgiveth; - this verily is a bounden duty
  42,44,"But he whom God shall cause to err, shall thenceforth have no protector. And thou shalt behold the perpetrators of injustice, Exclaiming, when they see the torment, \"Is there no way to return"
  42,45,"And thou shalt see them when set before it, downcast for the shame: they shall look at it with stealthy glances: and the believers shall say, \"Truly are the losers they who have lost themselves and their families on the day of Resurrection! Shall not the perpetrators of injustice be in lasting torment"
  42,46,And no other protectors shall there be to succour them than God; and no pathway for him whom God shall cause to err
  42,47,"Hearken then to your Lord ere the day come, which none can put back when God doth ordain its coming. No place of refuge for you on that day! no denying your own works"
  42,48,"But if they turn aside from thee, yet we have not sent thee to be their guardian. 'Tis thine but to preach. When we cause man to taste our gifts of mercy, he rejoiceth in it; but if for their by-gone handy-work evil betide them, then lo! is man ungrateful"
  42,49,"God's, the kingdom of the Heavens and of the Earth! He createth what He will! and he giveth daughters to whom He will, and sons to whom He will"
  42,50,"Or He giveth them children of both sexes, and He maketh whom He will to be childless; for He is Wise, Powerful"